    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="988"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d988">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.731/295</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 28, 1915</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2 p. m.</hi>] </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1541. Your 739, December 11.<note n="1" xml:id="d988fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1914Supp#pg_524">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1914, Supplement, p.
                        524</ref>.</note> British Government now informs me that Meyer’s Atlantic
                    cotton code, 39th edition, may be employed in telegrams between the United
                    Kingdom and any country on the extra-European telegraph system. This does not
                    include British colonies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
